g/resource/Nine_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.94086580683935e-14, \"text\": \"Channel Nine\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McAvaney\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"his tradition\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 386}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"the channel\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"broadcast rights\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 472}, {\"ngram\": \"a bidding war\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 496}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the commentating hero will not be part of rival Nine's Olympics coverage and will be covering radio commentary for the ABC instead.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9961135044192757, \"rank\": 0.003482687489860781, \"text\": \"ABC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the commentating hero\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"rival Nine's Olympics coverage\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"radio commentary\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 646}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McAvaney will be behind the mic calling the athletics portion of the games alongside Aussie Olympics stars like ex-sprinter Melinda Gainsford-Taylor and Olympic gold medalist Sarah Ryan.\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 793, \"end\": 817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melinda_Gainsford-Taylor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melinda Gainsford-Taylor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melinda_Gainsford-Taylor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melinda_Gainsford-Taylor\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McAvaney\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletics portion\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"Aussie Olympics stars\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 829}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have always thought the Olympics was the ultimate event for an Australian broadcaster,\\\" McAvaney said in a statement Monday.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.8836379323060535, \"rank\": 0.12503047628658323, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate event\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"McAvaney\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 976}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To be given this opportunity by the ABC means a great deal to me.\\\"\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9961135044192757, \"rank\": 0.003482687489860781, \"text\": \"ABC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this opportunity\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"a great deal\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regarded as \\\"the voice of footy\\\" for his work calling the AFL, the 71-year-old earlier retired from commentating football in 2021 but continues to host select events, including last year's Women's FIFA World Cup.\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999995107901956, \"rank\": 4.892048260625126e-07, \"text\": \"AFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Football_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.998763898976368, \"rank\": 0.0010907743568985757, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}, {\"begin\": 1257, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.997947675777537, \"rank\": 0.0011982183582779334, \"text\": \"World Cup\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the voice\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"footy\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"his work\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"select events\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps most memorably, McAvaney covered Cathy Freeman's iconic gold medal run in Sydney during the 2000 Olympics and became part of the fabric of the country's sporting history.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cathy_Freeman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cathy Freeman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cathy_Freeman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cathy_Freeman\"}, {\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999055790267972, \"rank\": 9.441242013497187e-05, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McAvaney\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1301}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2000 Olympics\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"the fabric\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's sporting history\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ABC decision salvages McAvaney's remarkable forty-year run commentating every Summer Olympic Games from the Soviet-era Moscow games in 1980 to the most recent Tokyo games in 2021.\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9961135044192757, \"rank\": 0.003482687489860781, \"text\": \"ABC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999995578656193, \"rank\": 3.1783959484371687e-07, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999345520812, \"rank\": 6.542433475244223e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McAvaney's remarkable forty-year run\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"every Summer Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nine maintains exclusive broadcasting rights to the Games and haspromised wall-to-wall two viewing on 24-hour free-to-air channelsas well as comprehensive streaming coverage.\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"exclusive broadcasting rights\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"wall\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"air\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"comprehensive streaming coverage\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The network paid about $305 million last year to secure the exclusive rights to broadcast the next five Summer and Winter Olympic Games on its Nine Networks and Stan assets, including the 2032 Brisbane Games.\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1953, \"end\": 1957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.927391049468153e-24, \"text\": \"Nine\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The network\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"the exclusive rights\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"the next five Summer and Winter Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2032 Brisbane Games\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nine also has the rights to the radio broadcast for the Olympics but agreed to sub-license rights to ABC radio in select regional markets.\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2158